rd for “meaningful server/client coverage.” I want to make sure I'm following the right approach, so I'll need to think this through carefully!\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering resource dependencies**\\n\\nI’m thinking about whether the failure is due to missing resource metadata generated externally by TCK. Should we generate a config file that includes all test resources? But maybe it's not necessary since the generated config is currently empty and the plugin may not update automatically. It seems to scan `sourceSets.test.resources`, so adding a resource should include it. Should we avoid external resources to prevent needing Native Image metadata? The test is about resource access, after all! We could use a custom ClassLoader to return a URL to a temp file, which might be a good workaround. However, the rule suggests not depending on Native Image metadata for temporary paths and advises using normal file APIs instead.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Evaluating resource access methods**\\n\\nI'm considering if using a custom ClassLoader to get a resource that returns a file URL to a temp file would still count as using classloader resource lookup for that temp path. This method doesn't depend on Native Image resource metadata but does involve a classloader. The typical approach would be to use resources in `src/test/resources`, which generates the necessary metadata. It seems like the core issue is about missing metadata. I wonder if using a custom ClassLoader means that metadata isn't required since the agent would log resource patterns, even for resource names.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_h8KmW6u522kGWNx0jpZzzLB0|fc_076145da7f8503f2016a3f8ba29db881968f771fa2d1f1d0fb", "name": "read", "arguments": {"path": "metadata/com.typesafe.akka/akka-http_2.13/10.5.3/reachability-metadata.json"}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 814, "output": 1453, "cacheRead": 41472, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 43739, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1782549388940, "responseId": "resp_076145da7f8503f2016a3f8b8d6dbc819696830178aeaea023"}}
